    <name>
      <text>8.2.21 (Sum GP where num terms is not given)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Find the sum of the geometric progression \[{@u1@} {@u2@}+{@u3@}-\cdots {@u_fin@}.\]</p><p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>We are given the geometric progression \({@u1@} {@u2@}+{@u3@}-\cdots {@u_fin@}\).<br></p><p>We notice that \( u_1=a = {@a1@}\) and \( r = {@r@}.\)</p><p></p><p>We know that \( u_n= ar^{n-1}.\) In our case \( {@u_fin@} = {@a1@} ({@r@})^{n-1}\) so \(n= {@n_val@}.\)</p>Using the formula \( S_n = \dfrac{a(1-r^n)}{1-r}\) for the sum of the first \(n\) terms, the sum of the first {@n_val@} terms is \[ S_{@n_val@} = \dfrac{a(1-r^n)}{1-r}= {@ta1@}.\]<p></p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
